<section xml:id="s_group_actions_orbits" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Group actions: orbits</title>

    <definition xml:id="d_orbits">
<title>Orbits</title>
<statement>
<p>
Let <m>G\times A\rightarrow A</m> be a group action. Given <m>a\in A</m>, we define its <term>orbit</term> <m>O_a</m> as 
<men xml:id="eq_orbit">
    O_a=\{a'\mid a'=g\cdot a \text{ for some } g\in G\}=\{g\cdot a\mid g\in G\}
</men>.
</p>
</statement>
</definition>
<definition xml:id="d_transitive">
<title>Transitive group action</title>
<statement>
<p>
A group action <m>G\times A\rightarrow A</m> is transitive if for all <m>a,a'\in A</m> there is a <m>g\in G</m> satisfying <m>a'=g\cdot a</m>. 
</p>
</statement>
</definition>
<theorem xml:id="th_index_p">
<title>Subgroups of prime index</title>
<statement>
<p>
Let <m>G</m> be a finite group and let <m>p</m> be the smallest prime divisor of <m>\abs{G}</m>. If <m>H</m> is a subgroup of <m>G</m> of index <m>p</m>, then <m>H</m> is normal. 
</p>
</statement>
<proof>
<p>
</p>
</proof>
</theorem>


<theorem xml:id="th_transitive_action">
<title>Orbit-stabilizer</title>
<statement>
<p>
Let <m>G\times A\rightarrow A</m> be a group action.
<ol>
    <li>
        <p>
            For all <m>a\in A</m>, the function 
            <md>
                <mrow>f\colon G/G_a \amp \rightarrow O_a</mrow>
                <mrow>gG_a \amp \mapsto g\cdot a</mrow>
            </md>
            is an isomorphism of <m>G</m>-sets, where <m>G</m> acts on <m>G/G_a</m> by left multiplication, and the action of <m>G</m> on <m>O_a</m> is given by restriction. 
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>
            For all <m>a\in A</m> we have 
            <men xml:id="eq_orbit-stabilizer">
                \abs{O_a}=[G\colon G_a]
            </men>.
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>
</p>
</statement>
<proof>
<p>
</p>
</proof>
</theorem>
<theorem xml:id="th_orbit_decomp">
<title>Orbit decomposition theorem</title>
<statement>
<p>
Let <m>G\times A\rightarrow A</m> be a group action. 
<ol>
    <li>
        <p>
            The relation <m>a\sim a'</m> if and only if <m>a'\in O_a</m> is an equivalence relation whose equivalence classes are the distinct orbits <m>O_a</m> of the group action. As a result, we have a partition 
            <me>
                A=\bigcup_{a\in A}O_a
            </me>
            of <m>A</m> into disjoint orbits, and <m>O_a=O_{a'}</m> if and only if <m>a'\in O_a</m>.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>
            As a <m>G</m>-set,  <m>A</m> decomposes into a disjoint union of transitive <m>G</m>-sets, each of which is isomorphic as a <m>G</m>-set to <m>G/H</m> for some subgroup <m>H\leq G</m>. 
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>
</p>
</statement>
<proof>
<p>
</p>
</proof>
</theorem>

